data.enText: connected with life on earth and not with any spiritual life
the sorrows of this earthly life

before.chText: 常用于疑问句或否定句以加强语气
before.enText: often used in questions and negatives for emphasis

data.enText: There's no earthly reason why you shouldn't go.

data.chText: 我的意见会有什么作用呢？
data.enText: What earthly difference is my opinion going to make?

data.chText: 他根本就不可能得到这份工作。
data.enText: He didn't have an earthly chance of getting the job.

tr: of or belonging to or characteristic of this earth as distinguished from heaven
example: believed that our earthly life is all that matters

value.def: Earthly means happening in the material world of our life on earth and not in any spiritual life or life after death.

example.ex: ...the need to confront evil during the earthly life...
example.tran: 需要在尘世生活中直面邪恶

example.ex: They lived in an earthly paradise.

value.def: Earthly is used for emphasis in phrases such as no earthly reason. If you say that there is no earthly reason why something should happen, you are emphasizing that there is no reason at all why it should happen.

example.ex: There is no earthly reason why they should ever change...
example.tran: 他们完全没有必要作出改变。

example.ex: What earthly reason would they have for lying?...
example.tran: 他们到底为什么要撒谎呢？

example.ex: There's no earthly use saying it isn't true.
example.tran: 说它不是真的根本没有用。

value.tran: （用于no earthly reason等短语中表示强调）根本，绝对
